<br>
The grouping part is one thing I haven't had too much trouble with my mage so far but I can see a lot of ppl's ignorance later on down the road of not wanting us in group by stating something as false as our pets eat up too much exp which is total nonsense.  Especially at higher lvls I would love to have a mage in group w/ a Duel Wielding pet w/ burnout and dmg shield!  It cuts down on down time and damage to the group big time!  I know this from playing w/ a mage in kithicor at night w/ my wizzie and one other person in group.<br>
Another nice thing about mages and I have heard them complain as well but just looking at the stats its not bad at all is the modulating rods we summon at lvl 44.  225hp for 150 mana is a better hp/mana ratio than the shaman's own cannibalize which is 50 for 25.  It would be most useful to a cleric/druid/wizard for emergency heal and evacing (i've only evaced my group w/ my wiz only ONCE btw so its not an often thing like a lot of ppl think).  We also offer great dmg shields to cast on tanks and malise line like the shamans for lowering the resistances and will stack on enchanters debuffs.  True, a lot of what I have seen and read on the average summonings are quite useless really but there are a few that are in demand and helpful.  Bandages/food/water/mod rods/ and ive read ppl talking about the sword of runes and have seen ppl online auctioning for one.  The most important thing to have in group w/ a mage is the pet!  Trust me, I have noticed that by not allowing the pet to do more than 50 per damage he doesn't eat up hardly any exp at all and if the group is letting the pet do that much to a mob then its time to find other stuff to kill anyway hehe.  I have noticed the exp split when grouped w/ one other person and no pet is summoned too.  According to GZ (for what its worth) pets in group only eat up an average of ONE WHOLE PERCENT.<br>
<br>
I know in this post I compared the wizard against the mage a little bit but both classes are excellent in their own ways in groups as far as I am concerned and enjoy playing them both (especially the mage =)).  I hope this helps boost your confidence in the mage class and hope to see others input as well.<br>
<br>
Nadil, lvl 20 Mage<br>
